    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>LAS VEGAS SELECTS BOMBARDIER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bombardier Inc wins $200 million contract to design and build elevated monorail in Las Vegas, linking eight hotels and casinos along four-mile section of Las Vegas Boulevard; Bombardier will be paid additional $56 million to operate and maintain four driverless, nine-car trains on the line for five years after service begins in 2004 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bombardier Inc. of Montreal has won a $200 million contract to design and build an elevated monorail in Las Vegas, linking eight hotels and casinos along a four-mile section of Las Vegas Boulevard. Bombardier will be paid an additional $56 million to operate and maintain the four driverless, nine-car trains on the line for five years after service begins in 2004.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Bombardier Inc. of Montreal has won a $200 million contract to design and build an elevated monorail in Las Vegas, linking eight hotels and casinos along a four-mile section of Las Vegas Boulevard. Bombardier will be paid an additional $56 million to operate and maintain the four driverless, nine-car trains on the line for five years after service begins in 2004.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
        <p>WORLD BUSINESS BRIEFING: AMERICAS</p>
